1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,733
<i> This isn't over yet.</i>

2
00:00:01,933 --> 00:00:03,700
<i> We're just getting started.</i>

3
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:05,600
<i> Your mother deserves to die.</i>

4
00:00:05,767 --> 00:00:06,633
<i> How dare you!</i>

5
00:00:06,767 --> 00:00:08,567
<i>Why don't you conduct
an investigation?</i>

6
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:11,767
<i>So you'll find out
they were all in cahoots!</i>

7
00:00:11,933 --> 00:00:13,767
<i> Balong works for you?</i>

8
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:16,033
<i>Miss Annie, I believe
we have a bigger problem.</i>

9
00:00:16,133 --> 00:00:18,567
<i>Andrei is also
at the police station.</i>

10
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:21,300
What made you say that the Tius
<i> had something to do</i>

11
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> with my mother leaving me?</i>

12
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,933
<i>Divine was the owner
of Orchid Place.</i>

13
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,800
<i>Annie knows why
the building collapsed.</i>

14
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,433
<i> Your mother is a sellout.</i>

15
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:32,967
<i> Why, Andrei?</i>

16
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>Do you still believe
your mother is innocent?</i>

17
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,100
<i> You were covered in blood.</i>

18
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:40,667
<i>I did try to revive her,
Caroline.</i>

19
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,600
<i>That's why I came home
covered in blood.</i>

20
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,233
<i> No, I don't believe you.</i>

21
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:47,767
<i>Why don't you ask her lover,
Engr. Gilbert Bautista?</i>

22
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:49,100
<i> My gosh!</i>

23
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,933
<i>She's not just a mistress.
She's a thief, too!</i>

24
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:53,233
<i> Caroline, I'm not lying!</i>

25
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:59,500
["YOU'LL BE SAFE HERE"
BY RICO BLANCO PLAYING]

26
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:02,333
<i>Keep me away
from all of this, Bingo.</i>

27
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:04,133
<i> I'm right here.</i>

28
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:06,100
<i> I'll never leave you.</i>

29
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,800
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:55,500
Ling.

31
00:01:55,667 --> 00:01:57,167
Are you hungry?
Do you want to eat?

32
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:59,333
Take a shower?
Tell me what you need.

33
00:01:59,433 --> 00:02:01,500
I just want peace, Bingo.

34
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:02,700
Peace.

35
00:02:02,867 --> 00:02:03,900
Have a seat.

36
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:06,567
I'll prepare your room
so you can get some rest.

37
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:07,467
[NENE YAWNS]

38
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:08,333
Oh!

39
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:10,367
Lingling?!

40
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,667
Lingling, my dear!

41
00:02:12,767 --> 00:02:14,200
Lingling!

42
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:18,833
Oh my! You're here.

43
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:20,067
What is she doing here?

44
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:23,200
Ling will be staying here
for a while, Grandma.

45
00:02:23,367 --> 00:02:24,400
[INHALES SHARPLY]

46
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:27,867
Did you two elope?

47
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:30,733
Oh, yes! Yes!

48
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,933
Grandma, what are you saying?
We didn't elope!

49
00:02:33,067 --> 00:02:34,533
I'm sorry about that.

50
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:35,533
[NENE LAUGHS]

51
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:38,533
I just need to breathe, Grandma.

52
00:02:41,433 --> 00:02:43,700
Of course,
you can stay here.

53
00:02:43,867 --> 00:02:44,600
Of course.

54
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:53,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,733
I'll just prepare your room.

56
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:18,033
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]
- [EXHALES DEEPLY]

57
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:19,533
[GINA] Are you sure about this?

58
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:21,933
<i> How will we do it?</i>

59
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:26,600
<i> It's simple.</i>

60
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:31,267
<i>Divine will be putting up
a building for GLC.</i>

61
00:03:31,433 --> 00:03:32,900
<i> The Orchid Place.</i>

62
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,267
<i>Wilson entrusted her
with this business.</i>

63
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:37,400
<i> And...</i>

64
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,300
<i> we will make her look bad.</i>

65
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,933
<i> Like, how bad?</i>

66
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:46,467
<i>We'll make it look like
Divine is a thief.</i>

67
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:48,933
<i>But we will be needing someone
from the inside.</i>

68
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:51,567
<i> Leave that to me.</i>

69
00:03:52,467 --> 00:03:55,100
<i>I know someone who
can fake the documents.</i>

70
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:57,833
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

71
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:58,833
<i> Get in.</i>

72
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:00,800
<i> It's the full payment.</i>

73
00:04:01,567 --> 00:04:03,467
<i> Just like what we agreed on.</i>

74
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:18,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,700
[WILSON] This would ruin us.

76
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:21,800
<i> It's all my fault.</i>

77
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:24,467
<i> So many people died.</i>

78
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:26,433
<i> Wilson.</i>

79
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,033
<i> It's not your fault.</i>

80
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:31,967
<i> It's Divine.</i>

81
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:33,500
<i> She's to blame for all this.</i>

82
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:35,833
<i> She used substandard materials</i>

83
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:37,333
<i> just to steal from you.</i>

84
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,167
<i> What?</i>

85
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:42,667
<i> You still don't believe me?</i>

86
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:46,000
<i> See for yourself!</i>

87
00:04:46,867 --> 00:04:49,667
<i>What other proof
do you need, Wilson?</i>

88
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:54,200
<i>She stole from you
just to be with her lover.</i>

89
00:04:54,367 --> 00:05:01,400
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:05:04,267 --> 00:05:05,033
[THUD]

91
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:21,567
[RAIN POURING, THUNDER CRASHING]

92
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:28,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:05:31,267 --> 00:05:32,367
<i> Charleston?</i>

94
00:05:32,467 --> 00:05:39,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:55,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:05,100
[SIGHS]

97
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:12,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,100
Are you okay?

99
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:22,767
I just wanted
to check on you.

100
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,433
[CINDY WHIMPERS]

101
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:35,767
I will do everything in my power

102
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:38,067
to protect all of you.

103
00:06:38,167 --> 00:06:45,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:56,800
Don't you think that
something fishy is going on?

105
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,167
What are you
talking about, Irene?

106
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:01,633
No, like...

107
00:07:01,733 --> 00:07:03,033
It's not impossible

108
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:05,300
that she was a mistress
and a thief, but...

109
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:09,300
what about Mama being covered
in blood after she came home

110
00:07:09,467 --> 00:07:11,467
from Auntie Divine's house

111
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:13,933
the night that she died?

112
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,300
[SIGHS] Okay, Irene.

113
00:07:15,433 --> 00:07:17,467
- Get straight to the point.
- Okay.

114
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:18,900
Like, come on!

115
00:07:19,867 --> 00:07:22,167
Do you honestly believe that
Mama would hug Caroline's mom?

116
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:23,167
[SCOFFS]

117
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:24,633
And even try to revive her?

118
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:26,533
We both know that's BS!

119
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:28,533
Do you buy it?

120
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,733
What if...

121
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:33,833
What if Mama had
something to do--

122
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,833
Irene.

123
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:36,567
Please.

124
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:39,200
Don't you dare say it.

125
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:40,967
But you said it yourself

126
00:07:41,067 --> 00:07:42,800
that she should've just
told Caroline the truth

127
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,567
so she would stop
all this drama.

128
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:46,733
Right?

129
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:49,467
You heard what Mama said, Irene.

130
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:52,867
She did everything
for this family.

131
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:55,433
And unfortunately,
that includes Caroline.

132
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:56,733
So quit it.

133
00:07:59,033 --> 00:07:59,867
Okay.

134
00:08:01,267 --> 00:08:02,833
Okay, I was just wondering.

135
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:06,233
You know how crazy
this family can get.

136
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:12,033
Yeah.

137
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:14,067
Yeah, whatever.

138
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:21,033
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

139
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:40,467
[BALONG] Damn you, Wilson Tiu!

141
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,233
<i>You know what happened
to Orchid Place.</i>

142
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,567
<i>That building collapsed
and killed many people,</i>

143
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:46,400
<i> including my wife.</i>

144
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,900
<i> And you, Caroline!</i>

145
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:51,267
<i> Your mother deserves to die!</i>

146
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:53,700
<i> They were all in cahoots!</i>

147
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,267
<i> Good riddance!</i>

148
00:08:55,467 --> 00:08:57,467
I tried to revive her Caroline.

149
00:08:57,633 --> 00:08:59,267
<i>That's why I came home
covered in blood.</i>

150
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:09,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:09:13,633 --> 00:09:15,100
<i> You mother is a sellout.</i>

152
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:21,333
<i>She worked for
Caroline's mom, Divine.</i>

153
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:24,100
[CAROLINE CRYING]

154
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,933
<i>Keep me away from
all of this, Bingo.</i>

155
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:35,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:52,333
[MUSIC FADING]

157
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:05,967
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:10:24,667 --> 00:10:26,500
Gilbert Bautista.

159
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,800
[CINDY]
<i> Why don't you ask her lover,</i>

160
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,133
<i> Engr. Gilbert Bautista?</i>

161
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,700
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

162
00:10:36,267 --> 00:10:43,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

163
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:22,800
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,567
[GASPS]

165
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:46,567
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:47,900
Ling.

167
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,400
I didn't know you were
still up.

168
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,300
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

169
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:53,333
Wait.

170
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:57,167
Take a look at this, Bingo.

171
00:11:57,300 --> 00:12:04,167
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,167
"The Orchid Place Tragedy:

173
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:13,800
Lives Lost in Building Collapse
Due to Faulty Materials."

174
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:17,267
Engr. Gilbert Bautista.

175
00:12:18,133 --> 00:12:20,133
You want to find this person?

176
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,333
Yes.

177
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:26,133
Auntie Cindy told me
about him.

178
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:28,867
That he was Mama's lover.

179
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:31,333
"Lover?"

180
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:33,467
As in, they had
a romantic relationship?

181
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,500
And you believe
your aunt Cindy?

182
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:38,433
Of course not.

183
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:42,267
But this Gilbert Bautista might
have the answers I need.

184
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:44,500
- Ling.
- Bingo.

185
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:48,000
I want to prove that Mama
wasn't at fault for everything,

186
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,300
like what Auntie Cindy
is accusing her of.

187
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:02,167
Ling, did my mom...

188
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:05,033
say anything else?

189
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:11,167
I mean, did she say
anything else

190
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:14,333
that can help you find the
truth about all this?

191
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,533
No.

192
00:13:18,067 --> 00:13:21,033
You heard everything she told me
at the golf course.

193
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:27,600
[BALONG]<i> Annie knows
</i> why the building collapsed.

194
00:13:27,733 --> 00:13:32,200
<i>In fact, she helped
sweep the issue under the rug.</i>

195
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:37,567
<i>All in exchange
for a huge sum of money.</i>

196
00:13:39,467 --> 00:13:41,400
[BINGO]<i> Of course,
</i> she would hide the truth.

197
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,233
<i> She was paid to do that.</i>

198
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,500
Bingo, maybe we should ask
people involved in real estate.

199
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,600
Ling.

200
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:55,533
- Take a breather first, okay?
- Bingo, I can't stop.

201
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:56,900
I won't be at peace.

202
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,467
I feel like I'm closer
to Mama's--

203
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,100
I know you're doing
all this

204
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:04,200
to give justice
to your mom's death.

205
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,033
But Ling...

206
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,467
Just relax for now.

207
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,733
You need to take
a break too.

208
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:13,033
After that, you can
fight again.

209
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:19,233
We won't let our problems
control our lives.

210
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:25,533
Whatever it is that happened
to our mothers in the past,

211
00:14:26,467 --> 00:14:29,400
just remember that they
are different from us.

212
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,133
We are not them.

213
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:39,433
Go drink your milk
so you can sleep.

214
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:42,333
Here. It's still warm.

215
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,167
Drink it.

216
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,267
Go ahead.

217
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,567
[SHERWIN] Alright. Okay.

218
00:14:53,667 --> 00:14:56,300
But please keep me updated
as soon as possible.

219
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:57,733
Okay.

220
00:14:57,833 --> 00:14:59,900
What did Balong
tell the cops?

221
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,933
What did he tell the Tius?

222
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,267
You said Andrei
was there, right?

223
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:06,967
Did he talk to Balong?
What does he know?

224
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:10,433
My contact at the station
is still looking into it.

225
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:14,633
Sherwin, you know
this could ruin my plans.

226
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:16,833
Miss Annie, I don't think
this has any effect

227
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,500
on what we have started.

228
00:15:18,667 --> 00:15:22,200
But the moment Balong
drags my name into all of this,

229
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:25,433
all my efforts
would go to waste.

230
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,633
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

231
00:15:28,733 --> 00:15:30,300
There's no other way then.

232
00:15:30,467 --> 00:15:33,200
Before they make a move
against me,

233
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:37,967
I need to speed up
the downfall of the Tius.

234
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:45,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,333
Aunt Cathy.

236
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:54,200
Wilson.

237
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:58,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

238
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,500
I need someone
to talk to.

239
00:16:01,667 --> 00:16:02,567
Come in.

240
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:08,067
Ling? Ling?

241
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:10,100
- [CAROLINE] Grandma.
- Oh. Here.

242
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:12,100
I brought you some clothes.

243
00:16:12,233 --> 00:16:14,400
They're brand new and I'm
sure you'll like them.

244
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:16,367
They're among the clothes
I sell.

245
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:20,200
Plus, I boiled some water
for you.

246
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:22,200
That way...

247
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:24,333
you can take
a hot bath.

248
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:26,433
- [CHUCKLES]
- Thank you, Grandma.

249
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:28,900
I'm sorry we don't
have a hot shower.

250
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:30,367
- It's okay.
- [CHUCKLES]

251
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:31,533
Where's Bingo?

252
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:35,533
Oh, he already left.
He had to go to work.

253
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,567
Miss, here's your package.

254
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:58,567
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:04,133
The results are all about
the collapsed building.

256
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:08,233
There's nothing else
about that engineer.

257
00:17:09,933 --> 00:17:11,267
Is he still alive?

258
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:15,767
I hope you didn't
tire yourself out.

259
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:17,500
No, I didn't.

260
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:18,900
How are you feeling?

261
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,433
I'm good.

262
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:24,167
Look. I make sure to drink
water on time.

263
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:28,433
I drink plenty of water
to cure my hematama.

264
00:17:28,533 --> 00:17:30,767
[LAUGHS]

265
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:33,233
Oh, something's wrong.

266
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,800
You didn't laugh
at my joke.

267
00:17:37,633 --> 00:17:40,267
I'm okay, Grandma.

268
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,333
That's what people who are not
okay would say.

269
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,633
Even though you're
not saying anything,

270
00:17:49,833 --> 00:17:53,467
I can sense
that you're hurting deep inside.

271
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:57,467
Grandma.

272
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:00,133
Why does it hurt so much?

273
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:04,167
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

274
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:08,767
It hurts because love
comes with pain.

275
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:14,100
Even though your family
is not perfect

276
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:18,600
and you sometimes find it hard
to love them,

277
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:22,967
your love for them
still remains.

278
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:25,000
I guess that's how it is.

279
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:27,167
The people we love
are also the ones

280
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:30,200
who can hurt us the most.

281
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:36,633
I'm not saying we should
disregard the pain,

282
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:40,700
but isn't it better if we
focus on love instead?

283
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:47,667
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

284
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:58,333
[MUSIC FADES]

285
00:19:00,967 --> 00:19:02,000
Wilson.

286
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:06,267
Have I gone deaf or are you
just sitting there silently?

287
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:13,200
I don't know where to start.

288
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:21,000
There's no beginning or end when
it comes to family problems.

289
00:19:22,033 --> 00:19:24,333
You will just have to take it
as they come.

290
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:31,733
My children are fighting over
who should be appointed as COO.

291
00:19:33,067 --> 00:19:36,967
Isn't that a sign that they want
to be part of your legacy?

292
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:41,267
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

293
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:44,900
But not at the expense
of destroying our family.

294
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,033
And then there's Caroline

295
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:52,567
and all her accusations about
the death of her mother.

296
00:19:52,667 --> 00:19:53,800
Wilson.

297
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:56,367
What do you expect?

298
00:19:57,567 --> 00:20:02,033
She will always be heartbroken
by her mom's death.

299
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,433
And you cannot take that
away from a child.

300
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:08,733
So, what should I do, Auntie?

301
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:13,333
I would've solved this already
if this was a business problem.

302
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:17,267
But it's not.
And you sometimes forget that.

303
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,600
In business,

304
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:25,433
decisions are strategic
and profit-oriented.

305
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:28,067
But when it comes
to family,

306
00:20:28,167 --> 00:20:31,600
every decision is made
out of love,

307
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:36,433
understanding, and taking care
of each other's welfare.

308
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:42,800
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:45,967
Give the COO position
to Caroline.

310
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:50,033
That will solve
all your problems.

311
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:57,033
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

312
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:08,300
<i>I used to mop at the warehouse
and the restaurant.</i>

313
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,700
<i>Just take a rest.
I got this.</i>

314
00:21:10,867 --> 00:21:13,333
- Don't you want me to go home?
<i> - Stay with me.</i>

315
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,533
<i>The voting tomorrow
will just be a formality.</i>

316
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,667
<i>Our eldest son
will have that position.</i>

317
00:21:18,767 --> 00:21:20,867
<i>If he really cares about you
as a brother,</i>

318
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,133
<i> ask him to back out.</i>

319
00:21:22,233 --> 00:21:23,500
<i> I'm begging you.</i>

320
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,900
<i>This position will help me
feel complete again.</i>

321
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:29,400
<i>The decision rests with you,
Mr. Wilson Tiu.</i>

322
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:31,667
<i>The farm we're going to visit
is near La Sinfonia.</i>

323
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:35,533
<i>They have products we can
include in Mabenta Box.</i>

324
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:38,000
<i>We'd like to make you
our business partner.</i>

325
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:39,567
<i> We can get local products</i>

326
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:42,400
<i>that we can distribute and
market all over the country.</i>

327
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:44,600
<i>If only the board members
of GLC could hear you,</i>

328
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:46,233
<i> I'm sure they'd be impressed.</i>

329
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,900
<i>I think it'd be nice
to live here</i>

330
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:50,567
<i>and enjoy a simple life
with your family.</i>

331
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:52,233
<i>Thank you for bringing
me here.</i>

332
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,067
<i>It means a lot to me.
I needed this.</i>

333
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:55,600
<i> I needed this too.</i>
